<html><div id="mwpage">
<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Summary</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">How to limit the number of events received in Operations Bridge Manager (OBM) during an upgrade with the primary goal being to make OBM operational as soon as possible. </span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The topics discussed in this document may introduce inconsistencies with the event state versus actual state and where possible these implications will be mentioned in the document.</span></span></span></p>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Problem</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The Web Data Entry (“wde”) process in OBM can potentially receive a large number of events during the period when OBM is offline during an upgrade. These events have to be processed on the Gateway and Data Processing Servers when OBM becomes fully operational again after an upgrade.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In scenarios where OBM will not be down for long periods during the upgrade (i.e. In the case of a side-by-side upgrade) then this document may not be as relevant compared to an in-place upgrade where the downtime is significantly more</span></span></span></p>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Cause</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Events can accumulate in a buffer file on an agent during OBM downtime. When OBM resumes working the buffered messages get forwarded by the message agent (opcmsga) on the monitored nodes to OBM. This can result in a large number of events being received in OBM which increases in proportion to the number of nodes monitored by OBM.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The types of events common in the OBM environment are discussed below:</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">System Infrastructure / Application monitoring events</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The events frequency is based on the policy interval, rules and suppression logic in the policy.<br>
An example of System Infrastructure event can be seen below:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-left:24px; margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_6024032abf7d87.45798263.png" style="width:520px; height:211px"></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Event data from various other management packs and/or custom policies will also send data to OBM</span></span></span></p>
&nbsp;

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Internal events generated by agent</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Internal events are also sent if an subagent (subagent; is a process which the agent runs to carry out specific jobs) malfunctions. The frequency of these events is unpredictable and largely depends on the stability of the Operations Agent.<br>
An example of some internal events can be seen below:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-left:24px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_6024032b46c2c7.52311698.png" style="width:601px; height:40px"></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:48px"></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Heartbeat events</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Heartbeat events are generated every 30 minutes by default and as long as the OBM server receives these events on a regular timed interval then no subsequent event will be seen in the event browser. Heartbeat events are mostly hidden from the user, however OBM still needs to process them.</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">ASSD events</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">ASSD events are sent upon activation of the agent and then 24 hrs or every restart of the opcmsga subagent process on the agent. This data is used to create/update the Operations Agent CI properties in RTSM/UCMDB.</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">AHSCollector events</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The agent sends Agent Health Events based on the self-monitoring of the agent. Self-monitoring occurs every 5 minutes by default and could result in an event if the status of the agent changes.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Example of an AHSCollector events can be seen below:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><img src="/mediawiki/images/pn_images/pn_image_6024032bcfd329.63573287.png" style="width:601px; height:57px"></span></span></span></p>
&nbsp;

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Event Reduction</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Various actions can be performed to reduce the number of events being sent whilst OBM is non-operational during the upgrade. Not all of these options maybe applicable but they are documented so as to provide the option to temporarily disable some features during the upgrade and should be implemented on a case by case basis depending upon your need.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In addition to the regular agent nodes these settings are also applicable for Operations Agent Connector (OpsCx) systems as well.</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Suppression of AHSCollector events</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">AHSCollector events can be disabled on an agent by agent basis with a configuration variable in agent.health namespace with the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The config variable <span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">OPC_SUPPRESS_SELFMON_EVENTS</span> is applicable from Operations Agent version 12.15 and above</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns agent.health -set OPC_SUPPRESS_SELFMON_EVENTS TRUE </span></span></span></span></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">Options for changing settings on multiple systems</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">opr-agt</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">opr-agt can be used to change a configuration variable on a remote agent or list of agent systems, e.g.:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var agent.health:OPC_SUPPRESS_SELFMON_EVENTS=TRUE -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">nodeinfo policy</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">A nodeinfo policy can also be used to set this configuration variable on remote agent nodes. The policy syntax is as follows:</span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[agent.health]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_SUPPRESS_SELFMON_EVENTS=TRUE</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">For the versions prior to 12.15 the only available option is to disable selfmon completely with the <span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">OPC_SELFMON_ENABLE FALSE </span>setting. This can be set on an agent by agent basis in the agent.health namespace as shown below:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns agent.health -set OPC_SELFMON_ENABLE FALSE </span></span></span></span></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">Options for changing settings on multiple systems</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">opr-agt</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">opr-agt can be used to change a configuration variable on a remote agent or list of agent systems, e.g.:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var agent.health:OPC_SELFMON_ENABLE=FALSE -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">nodeinfo policy</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">A nodeinfo policy can also be used to set this configuration variable on remote agent nodes. The policy syntax is as follows:</span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[agent.health]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_SELFMON_ENABLE=FALSE</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><i>Note: Consider disabling policies in batches rather than all nodes at once. For example, this could be done by disabling policies on a selection of nodes controlled by a CI Views / CI Collections where the total number of CIs does not contain all managed node but a sub-set.</i></span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">With the AHSCollector events disabled the self-monitoring events for OA will no longer be sent. The following documentation link details the health parameters affected - <a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.15/HVAppendix" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.15/HVAppendix</a></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">If OPC_SELFMON_ENABLE is set to FALSE then data will not be available in Health View dashboard in addition to suppression of the events from the self-monitoring of OA.</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Internal event suppression </span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Internal events can be suppressed by the config variable <span style="font-size:9.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#24292e">OPC_INT_MSG_FLT</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">To set this variable on a single agent use the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns eaagt -set </span><span style="font-size:9.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:#24292e">OPC_INT_MSG_FLT</span></span></span></span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"> TRUE </span></span></span></span></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">Options for changing settings on multiple systems</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">opr-agt</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">opr-agt can be used to change a configuration variable on a remote agent or list of agent systems, e.g.:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var eaagt:OPC_INT_MSG_FLT=TRUE -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">nodeinfo policy</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">A nodeinfo policy can also be used to set this configuration variable on remote agent nodes. The policy syntax is as follows:</span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[eaagt]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_INT_MSG_FLT=TRUE</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span lang="EN-US" style="background:white"><span style="color:#24292e">This setting will ensure all internal messages with message group “OpC” and “OpenView” be filtered.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span lang="EN-US" style="background:white"><span style="color:#24292e">A suitable internal msgi policy can be deployed to allowlist the necessary internal events.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span lang="EN-US" style="background:white"><span style="color:#24292e">One such allowlisted policy is shown in the following link which provides enhanced instruction text and better correlation amongst the internal events.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><a href="https://marketplace.microfocus.com/itom/content/oa-content-pack-for-internal-message-filtering" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">https://marketplace.microfocus.com/itom/content/oa-content-pack-for-internal-message-filtering</a></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:48px"></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">Monitoring Events</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">It is recommended to disable monitoring (i.e by disabling policies) in situations where policies are found to be noisy or alternatively add necessary suppression logic within the policies.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Example: Some measurement threshold policies with continue action configured may generate many redundant events. Such policies may need to be disabled.</span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Disabling policies might cause an issue for good/bad message correlation which could result in events in the active browser not matching the current state (because a good/bad message correlation event was missed)</span></span></span></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">COSO Event Forwarding</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">If events are suppressed/disabled or event forwarding to COSO is disabled then this could have an impact for COSO reporting as events maybe missed.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Post OBM downtime the disabled policies would require re-enablement.</span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"></h2>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Topology data</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In addition to event data, topology data is also sent to OBM via the following types of policies:</span></span></span></p>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Service Discovery policy (agtrep)</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Generic Topology policy (opcgeni)</span></span></span></li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Service discovery policy data is sent on an interval defined within each policy or when a change in topology is detected, and this data can also add to the load which requires processing by OBM.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Topology data streaming can be disabled during the OBM downtime by disabling the policies on the operations agents as follows:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">For service discovery policies (agtrep) the policy type is ‘svcdisc’ and the policies can be disabled with the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovpolicy -disable -poltype svcdisc</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">For generic topology discovery (opcgeni) the policy type is ‘xmltopo’ or ‘wsxmltopo’ and the policies can be disabled with the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovpolicy -disable -poltype xmltopo<br>
ovpolicy -disable -poltype wsxmltopo</span></span></span></span></p>

<h3 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#1f3763"><span style="font-weight:normal">Options for changing settings on multiple systems</span></span></span></span></span></h3>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">opr-agt</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">opr-agt can be used to remotely disable discovery policies by type:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username user -password passwd -cmd 'ovpolicy -disable -poltype &lt;svcdisc | xmltopo | wsxmltopo&gt;' -node_group mySAP | -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">opr-agt can also be used to remotely disable discovery policies by name:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username user -password passwd -cmd 'ovpolicy -disable -polname &lt;policy name&gt;' -node_group mySAP | -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The discovery policies where frequently topology changes are seen e.g. cloud/containerized environment can be exempt from disabling, to avoid loss of topology data.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">During the installation consider limiting the use of the following command as this will push topology data to OBM which will increase the amount of data which OBM has to digest when online again.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovagtrep -publish</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Any policies which are manually disabled need to be manually re-enabled after the downtime. </span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Agent Storm Detection</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The agent side storm detection and suppression config variables can also be set to reduce the number of messages in case of a storm situation, and therefore add to the load on OBM. Configuration of agent side storm detection is documented here:<br>
<a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.15/ConfiguringMessageStorm" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.15/ConfiguringMessageStorm</a></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<p></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The configuration variable <span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL</span> influences the frequency at which operations agent (opcmsga process) reaches out to OBM post the buffering scenario to confirm if OBM is reachable again, so as to resume message forwarding again. &nbsp;The default value is 60 seconds. It is recommended to set this value to 600 seconds during OBM downtime so that it provides ample time for OBM processes to startup before event generation starts from all managed nodes.</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">To set this variable for a single agent use the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns eaagt -set OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL 600</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The above command can also be executed remotely via ovconfpar if required as shown below</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">ovconfpar -set -ns eaagt -set OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL 600</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">opr-agt command can also be used to set the same on multiple nodes as shown below</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var eaagt: OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL=600 -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Else instead of using commands like ovconfchg, ovconfpar, opr-agt commands a nodeinfo policy could also be created with below contents and deployed to the remote nodes to update the settings.</span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[eaagt]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_MSGA_PING_SERVER_INTERVAL=600</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This will result in the time it takes to recover in case of any event forwarding issues to be prolonged for ten minutes instead of the default value of 1 minute. Hence it is recommended to revert the above setting to the default value after the OBM services are started completely.</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Avoiding agent message queue corruption</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Owing to the 2GB limit of the event queues on the agent nodes, it is recommended to configure a config variable to limit the message queue buffer size so that queue files do not become corrupted by breaching the 2GB limit. &nbsp;This especially important on nodes which send a lot of events which during the OBM downtime as they will generate a larger buffer file.</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Setting <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">OPC_BUFLIMIT_SIZE</span> to a maximum size of 1.9 GB will stop the buffer reaching the 2Gb limit.</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The command to set this on a single agent execute the following command:</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns eaagt -set OPC_BUFLIMIT_SIZE 1900000 </span></span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The above command can be executed remotely via ovconfpar if required as shown below</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">ovconfpar -set -ns eaagt -set OPC_BUFLIMIT_SIZE 1900000</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">opr-agt command can also be used to set the same on multiple nodes as shown below</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var eaagt: OPC_BUFLIMIT_SIZE=1900000 -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Else instead of using ovconfchg, ovconfpar, opr-agt commands nodeinfo policy can be created with the below mentioned contents and deployed to remote nodes to get the settings updated.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[eaagt]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_BUFLIMIT_SIZE=1900000</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">There are no implications when setting a maximum disk space utilization of 1.9 GB, however suitable disk space needs to be assigned to %ovdatadir% directory so as to be able to store a buffer file </span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">It is also the recommended for the configuration variable OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY “Minor” to be set. This ensures that when any subsequent events with severity of “Critical” or “Major” are received those events do not get discarded.</span></span></span></p>

<p></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The command to set this on a single agent is as follows:</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;">ovconfchg -ns eaagt -set OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY Minor</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The above command can be executed remotely via ovconfpar if required as shown below</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">ovconfpar -set -ns eaagt -set OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY Minor</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">opr-agt command can also be used to set the same on multiple nodes as shown below</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">opr-agt -username &lt;user&gt; -password &lt;passwd&gt; -set_config_var eaagt: OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY=Minor -node_list &lt;myNodeList&gt; | -view_name &lt;myView&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Else instead of using ovconfchg, ovconfpar opr-agt commands nodeinfo policy can be created with the below mentioned contents and deployed to remote nodes to get the settings updated.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<pre style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">;XPL config</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">[eaagt]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:3px; margin-bottom:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:#f3f3f3"><span style="line-height:15.0pt"><span style="tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:Consolas"><span style="color:#333333">OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY=”Minor”</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"></p>

<h4 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal"><span style="font-style:italic">Implications</span></span></span></span></span></span></h4>

<p style="margin-bottom:12px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">The </span><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">OPC_BUFLIMIT_SEVERITY </span></span><span style="color:black">setting will result in loss of events which have a severity less than configured. The above setting can be retained does not need to be reverted post the OBM downtime.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<h2 style="margin-top:3px"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2f5496"><span style="font-weight:normal">Additional Considerations</span></span></span></span></span></h2>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Operations Connectors also send events and as such need to be considered in the same way as agents are referenced in this document. </span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">COSO may miss data within the reports if events/metrics forwarding is disabled. </span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Incidents created by a ticketing service (e.g. Service Manager, etc) may not have any tickets created if the policies responsible for sending events are disabled.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:106%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">SLA reports maybe affected so operators need to be aware. </span></span></span></li>
</ul>
